Mercedes-Benz has revealed pricing for its top-of-the-line X-Class bakkie. The new models – the V6 X350d Progressive and Power – will sell for R904,188 and R973,188 respectively. “Mercedes-Benz has the pleasure of launching the first V6 double cab… the X350d 4MATIC,” said the company. “The X350d exudes the classical strengths in the X-Class range and depicts a modern vehicle, with a robust design, engineered for exceptional on and off-road capabilities and safety, with a signature stylish comfort finish.” Both models produce 190kW of power, have automatic transmissions, and 4×4 drive.